  "text": "Our results agree with previous studies [CITATION_1] , which found 30% artemisia oil was effective in maintaining leaf chlorophyll in chrysanthemum cut flowers. Philodendron plu jeeb leaves exposed to eucalyptus essential oil retain their free radical scavenging ability (Fig. 6) . Also, eucalyptus essential oil acts as an antioxidant that aids in defense against ROS, resulting in slowed chlorophyll degradation. Yellowing is a serious problem for cut leaves. Total carotenoid content decreased slowly in the 12.5 µg·mL -1 eucalyptus treatment compared with the controls (Fig. 5C ).",
